# claude-cron Framework — Vision

> Make the cron framework so good that agents can't drift.

## Purpose

This meta-cron monitors two project cron loops (ChengXing cron:1.0, KaiFeng cron:2.0) and continuously improves the ~/claude-cron/ framework itself. The goal: every project cron should follow the constitution reliably, produce ambitious sprints, and improve over time — without human intervention.

## Quality Bar

- Both project crons follow the constitution every cycle
- No health-check-only ticks — every cycle launches ≥8 explorers and ≥3 executors
- Framework templates are clear enough that agents don't misinterpret them
- When agents drift, the system self-corrects within 1-2 ticks

## Success Metrics

1. Compliance score ≥50/60 across both projects (averaged over last 10 ticks)
2. Zero "0 findings without discovery swarm" violations per day
3. Framework improvements propagate to both projects within 1 coherency cycle
